<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Taxonomic note.
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref17694">Emden (1958)</xref>
proposed the subspecies 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Limnophora (Calliophrys) riparia capoverdica</tp:taxon-name>
for the 
Cape Verde
population of the widespread Palearctic 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>L. riparia</tp:taxon-name>
, based on some differences in colour of the head and mesonotum and length of the aristal branches. On direct comparison of 
type
specimens (see above) with specimens from the Canary Islands and various European countries I found that the colour falls within the variation of the nominal species and that the difference pertaining to the arista is non-existing. Therefore, 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Limnophora (Calliophrys) riparia capoverdica Emden</tp:taxon-name>
is here considered as a synonym of 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Limnophora riparia (Fallén)</tp:taxon-name>
, 

<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->syn. nov.

</p>
